    "reason": "Issue #47 was a well-scoped enhancement with sound architectural fit (canary list → next-batch prepend → mark-completed gate → CLAUDE.md doc → tests). Implemented golden canaries as a regression-detection layer distinct from matrix sampling: tools/canaries.json seeds one cell per A/B/C/D/E/F role with pinned expected (role, defense_layer, did_user_get_tricked, outcome_status); cmd_next_batch prepends canaries with cell-id `canary-<id>-<role>` and `audience: canary`; _aggregate_batch splits canary records (filename prefix) so they never skew matrix counters and writes a separate `canaries` section in aggregate.json plus a CANARY VALIDATION / CANARY DRIFT block at the top of summary.txt; cmd_mark_completed runs aggregate before flipping status and refuses close-out on drift unless `--acknowledge-canary-drift` is passed (error message names three resolution paths). Added tests/suites/35-canaries.sh covering role coverage, prepending, drift on each field, missing-transcript drift, and the mark-completed gate. CLAUDE.md gained a 'Golden canaries — regression-detection layer' subsection. Backward-compat: _load_canaries returns [] when canaries.json is absent so existing test fixtures keep working without modification.",
